Stock_Twits_Sentiment_Analysis

Exploratory Data Analysis Plots for tweet counts

Density plot of normalized hourly percent change in sentiment score and price change

Plot p-values for linear regression fit model

Placeholder for Words Infographics

Heatmap

dat.plot <- 
  dat.byday %>% select(symbol, day, price, tweet_counts) %>%
  filter(day == "4/19/2016") %>%
  mutate(price=round(price)) %>%
  select(symbol, round(price), tweet_counts) 
View(dat.plot) 

rnames <- dat.plot[,1]                        # assign labels in column 1 to "rnames"
mat_data <- data.matrix(dat.plot[,2:ncol(dat.plot)])  # transform columns into a matrix
rownames(mat_data) <- rnames$symbol
my_palette <- colorRampPalette(c("red", "green"))
heatmap.2(mat_data,
          cellnote = mat_data,  
          main = 'Correlation', 
          notecol='black',     
          density.info='none',  
          trace="none",         
          #margins =c(2,2),     
          col=my_palette,      
          dendrogram='none',    
          cexColumn= 0.2,
          srtCol=0,   
          cexCol=1.0)
